    "author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
    "body": "To me, if you know a hidden file is there and you target it specifically by name, I see no reason you should _also_ be required to use -Force.\r\n\r\nIf you enter `%userprofile%\\appdata` under windows explorer you can still open the folder even though it's hidden, it doesn't tell you to \"please ask nicely first\". If you know it's there and you target it explicitly, requiring `-Force` is a bit of a silly additional requirement IMO.\r\n\r\nAs for \"why not change `ls`\", if you wanna do that, discussing it _here_ is pointless; head over to the folks maintaining those tools and ask them. ðŸ˜‚ ",
